{"title_page": "Seungri", "text_new": "{{other uses}}\n{{short description|South Korean singer}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Korean name|Lee}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name            = Seungri\n| image           = 181001 \uc2b9\ub9ac 02.png\n| image_size      = \n| caption         = Seungri in 2018\n| native_name     = \uc774\uc2b9\ud604\n| birth_name      = Lee Seung-hyun\n| birth_date      = {{birth date and age|1990|12|12}}\n| birth_place     = [[Gwangju]], South Korea\n| education       = \n| occupation      = {{hlist|Singer|songwriter|record producer|actor|businessman|investor|DJ|creative director}}\n| module          = {{Infobox musical artist\n| embed           = yes\n| background      = solo_singer\n| genre           = {{hlist|[[K-pop]]|[[J-pop]]|[[electropop]]}}\n| instruments     = {{hlist|Vocals|piano}}\n| label           = {{hlist|[[YG Entertainment|YG]]|Natural High|[[YG Entertainment#YGX|YGX]]}}\n| years_active    = 2005\u20132019<!--Please discuss on talk before changing-->\n| associated_acts = {{hlist|[[Big Bang (South Korean band)|Big Bang]]|[[YG Family]]}}\n| website         =\n}}\n| alias           = V.I\n| signature       = [[File:Seungri signature.png|100px]]\n| module2         = {{Infobox Korean name|child=yes\n| title           = [[Korean name]]\n| hangul          = {{linktext|\uc774|\uc2b9|\ud604}}\n| hanja           = {{linktext|\u674e|\u6607|\u70ab}}\n| rr              = I Seung-hyeon\n| mr              = Yi S\u016dnghy\u014fn\n| hangulstage     = \uc2b9\ub9ac\n| rrstage         = Seungni\n| mrstage         = S\u016dngni\n}}\n}}\n'''Lee Seung-hyun''' ({{korean|\uc774\uc2b9\ud604}}; born December 12, 1990),<ref name=\"Russell2014\">{{cite book|author=Mark Russell|title=K-Pop Now!: The Korean Music Revolution|page=34|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=etDZAwAAQBAJ|date=April 29, 2014|publisher=Tuttle Publishing|isbn=978-1-4629-1411-1}}</ref> better known by his stage names '''Seungri''' ([[Hangul]]: \uc2b9\ub9ac; ''Victory'') and '''V.I''' (when performing in Japan),<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://goboiano.com/original/1551-music-spotlight%25253A-big-bang|title=Music Spotlight: Big Bang|website=GoBoiano|accessdate=December 9, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151222093540/http://goboiano.com/original/1551-music-spotlight%253A-big-bang|archive-date=December 22, 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref> is a former South Korean singer, songwriter, record producer, actor, businessman, investor, DJ, creative director and rapist. In the mid-2000s, Seungri rose to prominence as one of three vocalists and youngest member of the South Korean boy band [[Big Bang (South Korean band)|Big Bang]] under [[YG Entertainment]], which eventually became one of the best-selling digital groups of all-time in Asia and one of the best-selling boy bands in the world.<ref name=\"records\">{{citeweb|url=https://variety.com/2017/digital/news/bigbang-kpop-youtube-red-reality-show-1202399581/|title=K-Pop Superstars BigBang Go Camping in YouTube Red\u2019s First Korean Show|work=[[Variety.com]]|accessdate=April 27, 2017|date=April 26, 2017|last=Spangler|first=Todd|publisher=[[Penske Media Corporation]]}}</ref> With the release of the group's second studio album [[Remember (Big Bang album)|''Remember'']] (2008), in which the second single released, \"[[Strong Baby]]\", was performed solely by Seungri, he began to adopt a more mature image as an artist.\n\nSeungri furthered this image with the release of his first [[extended play]], ''[[V.V.I.P]]'' in 2011. The EP debuted at number one on the [[Gaon Album Chart]] and yielded two singles: \"VVIP\" and \"What Can I Do\" (Korean: \uc5b4\uca4c\ub77c\uace0; Revised Romanization: ''Eojjeolago''). The latter peaked at number seven on the [[Gaon Digital Chart]] and the album sold over 50,000 copies.<!--48,682 in Korea + 2,114 in Japan--> His second Korean EP ''[[Let's Talk About Love (EP)|Let's Talk About Love]]'' (2013) fared better, becoming his second number one album and selling over 80,000 copies.<!--79,222 in Korea + 2,854 in Japan--> ''Let's Talk About Love'' was supported by \"Gotta Talk to You\" (Korean: \ud560\ub9d0 \uc788\uc5b4\uc694; Revised Romanization: ''Halmal Isseoyo''), which charted at number three on the Gaon Chart and was later re-released in Japan as his first full Japanese studio album, containing previous materials from the two EPs recorded in the country's native language. In 2018, he released his first Korean studio album, the chart-topper ''[[The Great Seungri]]'' and embarked on his [[The Great Seungri (tour)|first world tour]] as a solo artist.\n\nMaking his theatrical debut with the musical ''Sonagi'' in 2008, Seungri went on to star in films such as ''[[19-Nineteen|Nineteen]]'' and ''Why Did You Come to My House?'', both released in 2009. He branched into television with the Japanese drama ''Kindaichi Shonen no Jikenbo'' (2013) and the South Korean television series [[Angel Eyes (TV series)|''Angel Eyes'']] (2014). In recent years, he's explored other ventures, including opening a dance academy, owning a nightclub and restaurant franchise, founding a record label and investing in other businesses.\n\nOn March 11, 2019, Seungri departed from Big Bang and the entertainment industry and retired after allegations of him supplying prostitutes in 2015; a police investigation is ongoing into the [[Burning Sun scandal]].\n\n== Biography ==\n\n===Early beginnings and debut with Big Bang===\n[[File:Seung in Thailand.jpg|thumb|upright|Seungri at the TV show ''Fast Forward'' in [[Thailand]] in December 2007]]\n\nBorn and raised in [[Gwangju]], South Korea, Seungri was noted for his dancing skills growing up,<ref name=\"YG\uc2e0\uc778 \ube45\ubc45, '\ubc30\ud2c0\uc2e0\ud654' \ud0c8\ub77d\uc790 \ud3ec\ud568 '\ub208\uae38'\">{{cite news | first= | last= | author2= | title=YG\uc2e0\uc778 \ube45\ubc45, '\ubc30\ud2c0\uc2e0\ud654' \ud0c8\ub77d\uc790 \ud3ec\ud568 '\ub208\uae38'|date=July 7, 2006| publisher= | url =http://star.mt.co.kr/stview.php?no=2006070620255845157&type=3| work= Star News| pages = | accessdate = January 22, 2010 }}</ref> with the singer participating in the dance group II Hwa.<ref name=\"Seung Ri\">{{cite news| title=Seung Ri| url=http://www.koreanmovie.com/Seung_Ri_ka3268/| work=Koreanmovie.com| accessdate=January 22, 2010| url-status=dead| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100105165134/http://www.koreanmovie.com/Seung_Ri_ka3268/| archivedate=January 5, 2010| df=mdy-all}}</ref> Hoping to pursue a career in the entertainment industry, Seungri appeared in survival program ''Let's Coke Play! Battle Shinhwa'', a [[Reality television|reality television series]] to find the next [[Shinhwa]]. He was eventually eliminated in the ninth episode.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.bntnews.co.uk/app/news.php?nid=15500|title=[Past And Present] The Youngest But A Strong Baby, Seungri|website=BNTNews UK|access-date=May 10, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ib-article.com/2012/08/biography-of-big-bang-korean-boyband.html|title=Biography of Big Bang~Korean Boyband ~ My Article|website=www.ib-article.com|access-date=May 10, 2016}}</ref> Following his appearance on the show, Seungri was scouted by [[YG Entertainment]] to audition for the new boy band, [[Big Bang (South Korean band)|Big Bang]], alongside five other members: [[T.O.P (singer)|T.O.P]], [[Taeyang]], [[G-Dragon]], [[Daesung]], and [[Jang Hyun-seung|Hyun-seung]]. The formation of the group was documented on television.<ref name=\"Big Bang\">{{cite web|url=http://world.kbs.co.kr/english/entertainment/enter_artists_detail.htm?No=103896|title=Big Bang Profile|publisher=KBS World|accessdate=January 15, 2010|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090531185131/http://world.kbs.co.kr/english/entertainment/enter_artists_detail.htm?No=103896|archivedate=May 31, 2009}}</ref> Despite the initial plan of debuting six members, Seungri and Hyun-seung risked elimination due to their lack of stage presence and were given one final opportunity to impress [[Yang Hyun-suk]], founder of YG Entertainment. While Seungri was picked to stay, Hyung-seung (who went on to debut with the boy band [[Beast (South Korean band)|Beast]]) was dropped before the official debut.<ref name=\"'\uc900\ube44\ub41c \uadf8\ub8f9' \ube45\ubc45, \ub300\ud3ed\ubc1c \uc608\uace0\">{{cite news|url=http://sports.chosun.com/news/news.htm?name=/news/entertainment/200607/20060708/67h18001.htm|last=|first=|date=July 7, 2006|work=Sports Chosun|publisher=|pages=|language=ko|script-title=ko:'\uc900\ube44\ub41c \uadf8\ub8f9' \ube45\ubc45, \ub300\ud3ed\ubc1c \uc608\uace0|author2=|accessdate=January 15, 2010}}</ref>\n\nFollowing the release of several single albums, Big Bang's first album [[Bigbang Vol.1|''Big Bang Vol.1 - Since 2007'']] was a moderate success. Seungri also recorded his first solo song \"The Next Day\" (Korean: \ub2e4\uc74c\ub0a0; Revised Romanization: ''Daeumnal'') for the album. The group's breakthrough came with the release of their first [[extended play]], ''[[Always (Big Bang EP)|Always]]'' (2007), which included the number one song \"[[Lies (Big Bang song)|Lies]]\" ([[Hangul|Korean]]: \uac70\uc9d3\ub9d0; [[Revised Romanization of Korean|Revised Romanization]]: ''Geojitmal''). The song went on to top major Korean music charts for a record-breaking seven consecutive weeks,<sup>[[Big Bang (South Korean band)|[3]]]</sup> and won the group the [[Mnet Asian Music Award for Song of the Year|Song of the Year]] award at the [[Mnet Asian Music Awards|9th Mnet Korean Music Festival]].<sup>[[Big Bang (South Korean band)|[4]]]</sup> Their following EPs followed its predecessor's footsteps: ''[[Hot Issue (EP)|Hot Issue]]'' yielded \"[[Last Farewell (Big Bang song)|Last Farewell]]\" (Korean: \ub9c8\uc9c0\ub9c9 \uc778\uc0ac; Revised Romanization: ''Majimak Insa'') while ''[[Stand Up (Big Bang album)|Stand Up]]'' spawned \"[[Day by Day (Big Bang song)|Day by Day]]\" (Korean: \ud558\ub8e8\ud558\ub8e8; Revised Romanization: ''Haru Haru''); both singles were chart-toppers.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newsen.com/news_view.php?news_uid=200034&code=100200 |title=\ube45\ubc45 \uc96c\ud06c\uc628\ucc28\ud2b8 8\uc8fc \uc5f0\uc18d 1\uc704 \uae30\uc5fc, JOO\ub3c4 2\uc8fc\ub9cc\uc5d0 7\uc704 \uc9c4\uc785 |date=January 21, 2008 |publisher=Newsen |language=ko |accessdate=February 1, 2008 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080209235612/http://www.newsen.com/news_view.php?news_uid=200034&code=100200 |archivedate=February 9, 2008 }}</ref><ref name=\"Big Bang's 'Day by Day' Sweeps J-POP Charts for Four Weeks2\">{{cite web|url=http://english.kbs.co.kr/mcontents/entertainment/1546222_11692.html |title=Big Bang's 'Day by Day' Sweeps J-POP Charts for Four Weeks |date=September 8, 2008 |publisher=KBS World |accessdate=February 1, 2008 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080924063830/http://english.kbs.co.kr/mcontents/entertainment/1546222_11692.html |archivedate=September 24, 2008 }}</ref> Seungri continued to hone his dancing skills by competing against bandmate Taeyang in several dance competitions, as well as against [[Super Junior]]'s [[Eunhyuk]], [[TVXQ]]'s [[U-Know|Yunho]] and [[Shinee]]'s [[Lee Taemin|Taemin]].<ref name=\"\uc2b9\ub9acvs\ud0dc\uc591 \uc124\ud2b9\uc9d1 \ub304\uc2a4\ubc30\ud2c0 \u2018\ube45\ubc45 \ub0b4\uc804\u2019\">{{cite news|url=http://www.newsen.com/news_view.php?uid=200901221050051001|title=\uc2b9\ub9acvs\ud0dc\uc591 \uc124\ud2b9\uc9d1 \ub304\uc2a4\ubc30\ud2c0 '\ube45\ubc45 \ub0b4\uc804'|last=|first=|date=January 22, 2009|work=Newsen|publisher=|pages=|author2=|accessdate=January 22, 2010}}</ref> He also choreographs a large portion of Big Bang's dances.<ref>{{in lang|ko}}STAR News. [http://star.moneytoday.co.kr/view/star_view.php?type=1&gisano=2007120811191544749 \ube45\ubc45, '\uc904\ub118\uae30\ucda4'\uc73c\ub85c \uad6d\ubbfc\ub304\uc2a4 \ub3c4\uc804 (Big Bang, going for 'Jump Rope dance' as the all-time dance] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090211080811/http://star.moneytoday.co.kr/view/star_view.php?type=1&gisano=2007120811191544749 |date=February 11, 2009 }} Retrieved March 10, 2008.</ref>\n\n===2008\u20132011: Solo career development, acting, and ''VVIP''===\n\nIn 2008, members of Big Bang began branching out to develop their solo careers. Seungri became the first member of Big Bang to act in a musical with ''Sonagi'' in 2008. He also ventured into hosting, becoming a host for [[Munhwa Broadcasting Corporation|MBC]]'s music program ''[[Show! Music Core]]'' alongside Daesung. After filming wrapped up, Seungri went back into the studio with Big Bang to record for their second Korean studio album, ''[[Remember (Big Bang album)|Remember]]'' (2008). The album was promoted with two singles: \"[[Sunset Glow]]\" (Korean: \ubd89\uc740\ub178\uc744; Revised Romanization: ''Byulkeun Noeul'') and \"[[Strong Baby]],\" a solo release by Seungri. In order to shed the \"youngest member\" image from Big Bang,<ref name=\"\ub9c9\ub0b4 \uc2b9\ub9ac\uac00 \ub9d0\ud558\ub294 \ube45\ubc45 \uba64\ubc84\ub4e4\uc740? \u201c\ud0d1\ud615\uc740 \ub9dd\ud0dc \ud560\uc544\ubc84\uc9c0\u201d\">{{cite news | first= | last= | author2= | title=\ub9c9\ub0b4 \uc2b9\ub9ac\uac00 \ub9d0\ud558\ub294 \ube45\ubc45 \uba64\ubc84\ub4e4\uc740? \"\ud0d1\ud615\uc740 \ub9dd\ud0dc \ud560\uc544\ubc84\uc9c0\"|date=January 11, 2009| publisher= | url =http://www.newsen.co.kr/news_view.php?uid=200901111546201002&code=100200| work= Newsen| pages = | accessdate = January 22, 2010 }}</ref> he promoted the single with a more mature look complete with a stylized dance.<ref name=\"\ud3ec\ud1a0\uc5d4\uc2b9\ub9ac, \u2018strong baby\u2019 \uce60\ub4ef \ub9d0\ub4ef\">{{cite news | first= | last= | author2= | title=\ud3ec\ud1a0\uc5d4\uc2b9\ub9ac, 'strong baby' \uce60\ub4ef \ub9d0\ub4ef |date=January 9, 2009| publisher= | url =http://www.newsen.com/news_view.php?uid=200901091813061002| work= Newsen| pages = | accessdate = January 22, 2010 }}</ref><ref name=\"\ube45\ubc45 \uc2b9\ub9ac \u2018\uc2a4\ud2b8\ub871 \ubca0\uc774\ube44\u2019 \uc194\ub85c \ud65c\ub3d9 \uc2dc\uc791 \u2018\uc139\uc2dc\ubcf5\uadfc\u2019 \uacf5\uac1c\">{{cite news| title=\ube45\ubc45 \uc2b9\ub9ac '\uc2a4\ud2b8\ub871 \ubca0\uc774\ube44' \uc194\ub85c \ud65c\ub3d9 \uc2dc\uc791 '\uc139\uc2dc\ubcf5\uadfc' \uacf5\uac1c| date=September 1, 2008| url=http://ask.nate.com/knote/view.html?num=1240532&d=0&l=&ps=kl&pq=| work=Nate| accessdate=January 22, 2010| url-status=dead| archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130111064838/http://ask.nate.com/knote/view.html?num=1240532&d=0&l=&ps=kl&pq=| archivedate=January 11, 2013| df=mdy-all}}</ref> He won his first triple crown for \"Strong Baby\" on [[Seoul Broadcasting System|SBS]]'s live music show ''[[Inkigayo]]''.\n\nWhen promotional activities for ''Remember'' ended, Seungri returned to acting and starred in his first film ''Why Did You Come to My House?'', playing the love interest of [[Kang Hye-jung]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/news/art/2008/07/201_27537.html|title=Big Bang Members Branch Out as Soloists|date=July 14, 2008|website=koreatimes|access-date=May 10, 2016}}</ref> He then starred in his second musical ''Shouting'', alongside bandmate Daesung, who was unable to perform at the last minute due to a car accident.<ref name=\"'\ube45\ubc45' \uc2b9\ub9ac, \ubba4\uc9c0\uceec '\uc18c\ub098\uae30'\ub85c \ubc30\uc6b0 \ub370\ubdd4\">{{cite news|url=http://star.mt.co.kr/stview.php?no=2008022215081710555&type=3|title='\ube45\ubc45' \uc2b9\ub9ac, \ubba4\uc9c0\uceec '\uc18c\ub098\uae30'\ub85c \ubc30\uc6b0 \ub370\ubdd4|last=|first=|date=February 22, 2008|work=Star News|publisher=|pages=|author2=|accessdate=January 22, 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://koreatimes.co.kr/www/news/nation/2009/08/398_50194.html|title=Victory Performs More Than His Role in Musical Shouting|date=August 16, 2009|website=The Korea Times}}</ref> The same year, he also starred in the film ''[[19-Nineteen]]'' alongside fellow member [[T.O.P]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/article.aspx?aid=2905143|title=Big Bang duo star in murder movie|date=May 22, 2009|website=Korea JoongAng Daily}}</ref>\n\nSeungri's first [[extended play]], ''[[VVIP]]'', was released on January 20, 2011 with two singles: \"VVIP\" and \"What Can I Do\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.tenasia.com/archives/5831|title=Big Bang Seungri unveils music videos for title tracks|date=January 21, 2011|website=TenAsia}}</ref> To establish an identity away from Big Bang through his music, Seungri involved himself in the production of the album, composing and writing six out of the seven songs.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.tenasia.com/archives/6053|title=[INTERVIEW] Big Bang member Seungri \u2013 Part 1|date=February 11, 2011|website=TenAsia}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.tenasia.com/archives/6052|title=[INTERVIEW] Big Bang member Seungri \u2013 Part 2|date=February 11, 2011|website=TenAsia}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.tenasia.com/archives/6051|title=[INTERVIEW] Big Bang member Seungri \u2013 Part 3|date=February 11, 2011|website=TenAsia}}</ref> \"VVIP\" and \"What Can I Do\" won a triple crown on [[Mnet (TV channel)|Mnet]]'s ''[[M! Countdown]]''. Seungri also won the SBS ''Inkigayo'' Mutizen Award. Promotional activities were cut short in order for Seungri to focus on Big Bang's [[Tonight (Big Bang EP)|comeback]]. The same year, he was cast in the MBC drama ''[[Lights and Shadows (TV series)|Lights and Shadows]]'', playing an aspiring singer from the country.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/article.aspx?aid=2945991|title=Seungri accepts role in MBC drama|date=December 22, 2011|website=Korea JoongAng Daily}}</ref>\n\n===2012\u20132014: Japanese promotions, hiatus, and ''Let's Talk About Love''===\n[[File:Seungri 2012.jpg|thumb|right|Seungri performing in 2012]]\n\nIn 2012, Seungri started his first Japanese promotions by appearing on variety shows, such as hosting a Japanese radio program entitled ''Big Bang's All Night Nippon''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/article.aspx?aid=2954761|title=Big Bang\u2019s Seungri to stand as solo artist in Japan|date=June 21, 2012}}</ref> He was also chosen as the special MC on [[Fuji TV]]'s ''Sakigake! Ongaku Banzuke Eight'', where he interviewed celebrities.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/article.aspx?aid=2957345|title=Seungri to host TV show in Japan|date=August 4, 2012|website=Korea JoongAng Daily}}</ref> He had his first Japanese show ''Seungchan's Complete Victory Declaration'' on [[Space Shower TV]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sg.style.yahoo.com/news/big-bang-s-seungri-gets-own-special-program-021009910.html|title=Big Bang\u2019s Seungri Gets Own Special Program and MC Role on Japan TV|date=August 3, 2012|website=Mwave}}</ref> Seungri later appeared in the Nihon TV special drama ''Kindaichi Shonen no Jikenbo'' to celebrate the 60th anniversary of the Japanese broadcasting company, [[Nippon Television|NTV]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/article.aspx?aid=2958847|title=Big Bang\u2019s Seungri in Japanese drama|date=September 4, 2012|website=Korea JoongAng Daily}}</ref> The drama was based on the manga ''[[The Kindaichi Case Files|Kindaichi Case Files Neo SP 1: Hong Kong Kowloon Treasure Murder Case]]'', and premiered in January 2013. It later won the Best Drama SP (Excellence Awards) at the Tokyo Drama Awards. He also became a regular cast of [[Music On! TV]]'s program ''Count Down E.T'', hosting the Men's Bar Food section.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.tenasia.com/archives/61145|title=Big Bang Seungri to Make Regular Appearance on Japanese TV|date=June 21, 2013|website=TenAsia}}</ref>\n\nSeungri's career took a setback when he became embroiled in a sex scandal with a Japanese woman. As a result, he stepped out of Big Bang's promotional activities for self-reflection.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/article.aspx?aid=2959465|title=Seungri caught up in sex scandal|date=September 15, 2012|website=Korea JoongAng Daily}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/article.aspx?aid=2959678|title=Seungri rocked by another scandal|date=September 20, 2012|website=Korea JoongAng Daily}}</ref>\nHe would revisit the scandal one year later on [[Seoul Broadcasting System|SBS]] talk show ''Incarnation'', discussing how it helped him grow up and how fans began to view him more as an adult.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Big Bang Seungri Opens Up About His Japanese Sex Scandal|url = http://www.kpopstarz.com/articles/39251/20130828/big-bang-seungri-sex-scandal.htm|website = KpopStarz|date = August 28, 2013|accessdate = December 9, 2015}}</ref>\n\nRecording for Seungri's second Korean EP ''[[Let's Talk About Love (EP)|Let's Talk About Love]]'' took over two years, and the artist also involved himself with the production of the album.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ygfamily.com/notice/NList.asp?LANGDIV=E&Page=4&n2PageSize=8&IDX=4161&sType=A&SchKey=&SchTitleN=|title=Announcement for SEUNGRI\u2019s 2nd mini album [LET\u2019S TALK ABOUT LOVE] release on August 21|last=YG Entertainment|first=|date=August 12, 2013|website=YG Entertainment|publisher=|access-date=May 11, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/article.aspx?aid=2976307|title=Big Bang\u2019s Seungri releases new album|date=August 20, 2013|website=Korea JoongAng Daily}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.tenasia.com/archives/70779|title=[INTERVIEW] Big Bang member Seungri|date=August 27, 2013|website=TenAsia}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.tenasia.com/archives/68869|title=Big Bang Seungri Unveils Story Behind New Album|date=August 13, 2013|website=TenAsia}}</ref>\nThe EP was released on August 19, 2013, debuting at number one on the Gaon Chart<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://bigbangupdates.com/2013/08/seungri-gaon-hanteo-chart.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160604010831/http://bigbangupdates.com/2013/08/seungri-gaon-hanteo-chart.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=June 4, 2016|title=Seungri's \u2018Let's Talk about Love\u2019 #1 on Gaon's Weekly Albums Chart|website=bigbangupdates.com|access-date=May 11, 2016}}</ref> and went on to sell over 70,000 copies.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/album.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=&targetTime=2013&hitYear=2013&termGbn=year|title=2013\ub144 Album Chart|website=Gaon Chart}}</ref> He promoted the singles \"Gotta Talk to You\" and the eponymous title track.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/k-town/5657837/bigbangs-seungri-displays-sophistication-on-gotta-talk-to-u-single|title=BIGBANG's Seungri Displays Sophistication on 'Gotta Talk To U' Single & New EP|date=August 21, 2013|website=Billboard}}</ref> In October of the same year, he released his first Japanese album, selling over 14,000 copies in its first day and topping the [[Oricon Charts]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://m.mwave.interest.me/en/kpop-news/article-print/47790/|title=Big Bang Seungri\u2019s Solo Album Ranks First on Japan\u2019s Oricon|date=October 10, 2013|website=Mwave|access-date=February 4, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180204182455/http://m.mwave.interest.me/en/kpop-news/article-print/47790/|archive-date=February 4, 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref> The album contained songs from his previous albums, as well as the new song \"The Feelings Painted in the Sky\" (Japanese: \u7a7a\u306b\u63cf\u304f\u601d\u3044), which was later used as the theme song for Seungri's first Japanese television drama ''Yubikoi \uff5eKimini Okuru Message\uff5e.''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.barks.jp/news/?id=1000094400|title=BIGBANG\u306eV.I\u3001\u521d\u306e\u65e5\u672c\u30aa\u30ea\u30b8\u30ca\u30eb\u66f8\u304d\u4e0b\u308d\u3057\u66f2\u300c\u7a7a\u306b\u63cf\u304f\u601d\u3044\u300d\u304cUULA\u30c9\u30e9\u30de\u306e\u4e3b\u984c\u6b4c\u306b\u6c7a\u5b9a|work=BARKS|accessdate=March 11, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://mwave.interest.me/en/enewsworld/en/article/52636/bigbang-seungri-writes-and-performs-japanese-drama-ost|title=Big Bang\u2032s Seungri Sings Drama OST for \u2032Yubikoi Kimini Okuru Message\u2032 Promo Event|date=December 5, 2013|website=Mwave}}{{Dead link|date=January 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\nIn September, Seungri joined ''Popular Women 100'' as a co-host alongside comedian [[Hiroshi Yamazaki]], becoming the first international celebrity to clinch a hosting spot on a regular cable show in Japan.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.tenasia.com/archives/73617|title=Big Bang Seungri Becomes 1st Foreign Host on Japanese Major TV Channel Shows|date=September 24, 2013|website=TenAsia}}</ref>\n\nFrom 2013 to 2014, Seungri starred in the Japanese drama ''Yubikoi ~Kimini Okuru Message~ - A Message Send To You''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mwave.interest.me/en/enewsworld/en/article/50454/big-bangs-seungris-japanese-drama-to-air-in-december|title=Big Bang\u2019s Seungri to Star in Japanese Drama|date=November 12, 2013|website=enewsWorld}}</ref> He then took a supporting role in the Korean medical drama [[Angel Eyes (TV series)|''Angel Eyes'']] alongside labelmate [[Ku Hye-sun]], playing the role of a Korean-American teen with the dream of becoming an emergency rescue worker.<ref>{{cite web|last=Kim |first=Jessica |title=Big Bang's Seungri Cast in Ku Hye-sun Drama |url=http://www.tenasia.com/big-bangs-seungri-cast-in-ku-hye-sun-drama/ |work=TenAsia |accessdate=March 10, 2014 |date=February 28, 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140329155627/http://www.tenasia.com/big-bangs-seungri-cast-in-ku-hye-sun-drama/ |archivedate=March 29, 2014 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Kim|first=Hee-eun|title=Seung-ri to make TV series debut|url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/article.aspx?aid=2985688|work=[[Korea JoongAng Daily]]|accessdate=March 10, 2014|date=March 3, 2014}}</ref>\n\n=== 2015\u2013present: Focus on acting, ''The Great Seungri'', tour and other activites ===\nThough he [[Made World Tour|toured]] extensively from 2015 to 2016 with his band to promote their third Korean album [[Made (Big Bang album)|''Made'']] (2016),<sup>[[Big Bang (South Korean band)|[105][106]]]</sup> Seungri also appeared as a professional judge on the Chinese TV program'' Girls Fighting'' in 2016, where he mentored trainees.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mwave.me/en/news/news/view/105843/Big-Bang%E2%80%B2s-Seungri-to-Appear-on-Chinese-Reality-Program|title=Big Bang\u2032s Seungri to Appear on Chinese Reality Program|website=Mwave|date=June 3, 2016}}</ref> He also produced the song \"36 Tricks of Love\" for the show, a remake of the Taiwanese singer [[Jolin Tsai]]'s song under the same title. The song took the number one spot on the [[QQ Music]] and Weibo charts in China.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.yg-life.com/archives/78327?lang=en|title=SEUNGRI\u2019s first Chinese song took No.1 on QQ chart\u2026 \"The power of fans in this continent is the best, really grateful\"|date=July 25, 2016|website=YG Life}}</ref>\nHe later starred in the Japanese movie, ''[[High & Low: The Movie]]'' (2016), playing the son of a Korean mob boss.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mwave.me/en/news/news/view/104764/Big-Bang%E2%80%99s-Seungri-to-Appear-in-Japanese-Movie|title=Big Bang\u2019s Seungri to Appear in Japanese Movie|date=April 22, 2016|website=Mwave|access-date=May 10, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.hochi.co.jp/entertainment/20160421-OHT1T50155.html|script-title=ja:\uff22\uff29\uff27\uff22\uff21\uff2e\uff27\u306e\uff36\uff0e\uff29\u304c\uff25\uff38\uff29\uff2c\uff25\u306e\u30ea\u30fc\u30c0\u30fc\u30fb\uff28\uff29\uff32\uff2f\u30d7\u30ed\u30c7\u30e5\u30fc\u30b9\u6620\u753b\u306b\u51fa\u6f14|date=April 21, 2016|website=\u30b9\u30dd\u30fc\u30c4\u5831\u77e5|language=ja-JP|access-date=May 10, 2016|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160423014304/http://www.hochi.co.jp/entertainment/20160421-OHT1T50155.html|archivedate=April 23, 2016}}</ref> The film was commercially successful, and placed second at the Japanese box office on its opening, grossing {{JPY|668.3 million}}.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.yg-life.com/archives/84333?lang=en|title=BIGBANG SEUNGRI\u2019s debut film in Japan is released in Korea on January 12|date=December 26, 2016|website=YG Life}}</ref> He also recorded the song \"We Run Dis\" with PKCZ for the soundtrack. In August 2016, he started filming for his first Chinese film ''Bonjour L'amour'' (also titled ''Love Only'').<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.yg-life.com/archives/77308?lang=en|title=BIGBANG\u2019s SEUNGRI kicks off career in Chinese movie scene\u2026 \"Working hard on Chinese now\"|work=YG Life|accessdate=January 27, 2017}}</ref> The movie was released on March 2, 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kpopherald.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=201802081430010023385_2|title=Big Bang\u2019s Seungri to star in Chinese film \u2018Love Only\u2019|date=February 8, 2018|website=Kpop Herald}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2018, Seungri announced his first solo tour [[The Great Seungri (tour)|The Great Seungri]], twelve years after his debut, with shows announced in South Korea and Japan, the tour is to support his first studio album.<ref>{{cite news|title=BIGBANG\u306eV.I\u3001\u65e5\u672c\u3067\u521d\u3068\u306a\u308b\u30bd\u30ed\u30c4\u30a2\u30fc\u300eSEUNGRI 1ST SOLO TOUR 2018\u300f\u958b\u50ac\u6c7a\u5b9a |url=http://top.tsite.jp/entertainment/k-pop/i/39833209/index|website=T-Site News|accessdate=June 7, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=[OFFICIAL] BIGBANG SEUNGRI Will Hold His First-Ever Solo Concert in 12 Years Since Debut\u2026 Date Confirmed as August 4\u00b75th|url=http://www.yg-life.com/archives/104781?lang=en|publisher=YG Life|accessdate=June 7, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Seungri soars as solo artist|url=http://www.thejakartapost.com/life/2018/06/06/seungri-soars-as-solo-artist.html|publisher=The Jakarta Post|accessdate=June 7, 2018}}</ref> Seungri was featured on the single \"Combo\" by TPA, with Al Rocco and [[Ivy (Chinese singer)|Ivy]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Combo, a song by TPA, Seungri, Al Rocco, Ivy |url=https://open.spotify.com/track/6q3Schw5DAKB213Sc7vVVH |website=Spotify |accessdate=February 27, 2020}}</ref> He released a second collaboration single \"Ignite\", with K-391, [[Alan Walker (music producer)|Alan Walker]] and [[Julie Bergan]]. The song topped the Norwegian chart for two weeks.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vglista.no/topplister/topp-20-single-2018-21/|title=VG-lista \u2013 Topp 20 Single uke 21, 2018|publisher=[[VG-lista]]|accessdate=May 25, 2018}}</ref> On July 20, 2018, Seungri released his first Korean studio album ''[[The Great Seungri]]'', with \"1, 2, 3!\" as its title track. Seungri was highly involved in the production of the album, co-composing and writing for all tracks. The album debuted at number one on South Korea's [[Gaon Chart]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/album.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=&targetTime=30&hitYear=2018&termGbn=week|title=Gaon Album Chart \u2013 Week 30, 2018|website=[[Gaon Music Chart|Gaon Chart]] |language=ko |accessdate=August 2, 2018}}</ref>\n\nSeungri also starred in [[YG Entertainment|YG]] and [[Netflix]]'s sitcom-variety show, ''[[YG Future Strategy Office]]'',<ref>{{cite web |url= http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/article.aspx?aid=3044822&cloc=joongangdaily%7Chome%7Conline |title= Netflix teams up with YG for a variety show |date= February 23, 2018| website=Korea JoongAng Daily}}</ref> playing a fictionalised version of himself appointed as senior adviser to the fictional division of YG Entertainment. The show debuted in October 2018.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.scmp.com/magazines/style/news-trends/article/2166780/comedy-show-yg-fso-starring-seungri-k-pop-band-big-bang|title= Comedy show 'YG FSO', starring Seungri of K-pop band Big Bang, to air on Friday on Netflix\n |date= October 3, 2018| work=South China Morning Post|accessdate= February 10, 2019}}</ref> In November of that same year, he joined the variety show ''[[We Will Channel You]]'' as a regular cast member.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://entertain.naver.com/now/read?oid=057&aid=0001298963|title= \ube45\ubc45 \uc2b9\ub9ac, \u2018\uac00\ub85c\ucc44!\ub110\u2019 \ud569\ub958\u2026\uac15\ud638\ub3d9\uc5d0 \uba39\uce60 \uc124\uc695\uc804(\uacf5\uc2dd\uc785\uc7a5)|date= November 11, 2018| work=MBN Korea|accessdate= February 10, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Controversy and departure==\n{{further|Burning Sun scandal}}\n\nIn 2019, a number of allegations related to club Burning Sun, a nightclub founded in 2018 and managed by two CEOs; Lee Moon-ho and Lee  Seong-hyun.<ref name=\"\ub2e8\ub3c5 \ubb3c\uac8c\uac00 \ud544\uc694\ud574\u2026\uc2b9\ub9ac\ub9cc \ubaa8\ub974\ub294, '\ubc84\ub2dd\uc36c' \ub300\ud654\ubc29\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.dispatch.co.kr/2004109|title=[\ub2e8\ub3c5] \"\ubb3c\uac8c\uac00 \ud544\uc694\ud574\"\u2026\uc2b9\ub9ac\ub9cc \ubaa8\ub974\ub294, '\ubc84\ub2dd\uc36c' \ub300\ud654\ubc29|date=February 3, 2019|website=\ub514\uc2a4\ud328\uce58 {{!}} \ub274\uc2a4\ub294 \ud329\ud2b8\ub2e4!|language=ko-KR|access-date=August 19, 2019}}</ref> surrounded the singer Seungri due to his affiliation with the business as a creative director/shareholder<ref name=\"\ub2e8\ub3c5 \ubb3c\uac8c\uac00 \ud544\uc694\ud574\u2026\uc2b9\ub9ac\ub9cc \ubaa8\ub974\ub294, '\ubc84\ub2dd\uc36c' \ub300\ud654\ubc29\"/> and occasional DJ. The allegations included drug use and arranging sexual favors for investors, among others. KakaoTalk conversations of the singer with a Burning Sun co-founder and another of its employees about such arrangements were revealed by media in relation to the prostitution allegation, but the original, unedited KakaoTalk messages were not submitted according to the police during a press conference on March 4.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/article.aspx?aid=3060172|title=Gov\u2019t has Seungri\u2019s sordid texts|website=Korea JoongAng Daily|access-date=August 19, 2019}}</ref> Seungri also denied the allegations. On March 10, Seungri underwent a second round of drug analysis; hair and urine samples were tested, and the results were negative.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://n.news.naver.com/entertain/article/477/0000167845|title=\uc2b9\ub9ac, \uc131\ub9e4\ub9e4 \uc54c\uc120 \ud610\uc758\ub85c '\uacbd\ucc30 \uc785\uac74'\u2026\ub9c8\uc57d\ub958 \uac80\uc0ac\ub294 '\uc74c\uc131 \ubc18\uc751' [\uc885\ud569]|website=n.news.naver.com|language=ko|access-date=August 19, 2019}}</ref> On March 11, Seungri announced on his Instagram account of his retirement from the entertainment industry, stating that he would fully cooperate with the investigation. This led to the consentual termination of his contract with his agency YG Entertainment on March 13.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://star.hankookilbo.com/News/Read/201903131252013695|title=YG \uce21 \"\uc2b9\ub9ac \uc694\uccad\uc5d0 \uacc4\uc57d \uc885\ub8cc, \ub300\ub300\uc801 \uccb4\uc9c8 \uac1c\uc120 \ud544\uc694\uc131 \uc808\uac10\" [\uc804\ubb38]|website=\ud55c\uad6d\uc77c\ubcf4|language=ko|access-date=August 19, 2019}}</ref> On April 1, the Seoul Metropolitan Police Agency reported that Seungri and his business partner Yoo In-seok (co-CEO of Yuri Holdings) embezzled funds from Yuri Holdings for business purposes. The amount was reported to be about tens of millions of won (10M KRW \u2248 US$8400).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/now/read?oid=421&aid=0003912383|title=\"\uc2b9\ub9ac\u00b7\uc720\uc778\uc11d, \uc720\ub9ac\ud640\ub529\uc2a4 \uc790\uae08 \ud6a1\ub839 \uc758\ud639 \ucd94\uac00 \uc785\uac74\"|website=entertain.naver.com|language=ko|access-date=August 19, 2019}}</ref> On April 25, Seungri denied the prostitution charges related to a 2015 Christmas party, however Yoo In-seok admitted that he called and paid for entertainers for Japanese investors. The hotel bill was reportedly paid using a YG Entertainment corporate card, however Seungri denied knowing about the occurrence of prostitution.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://news.naver.com/main/read.nhn?mode=LSD&mid=sec&oid=025&aid=0002902604&sid1=001|title=\ud638\ud154\ube44 3000\ub9cc\uc6d0 \uacb0\uc81c\u2026\uc2b9\ub9ac, \uc131\uc811\ub300 \uc815\ub9d0 \ubab0\ub790\ub098|website=news.naver.com|language=ko|access-date=August 19, 2019}}</ref> On May 8, after a total of 17 closed-door police interrogations, the Seoul Metropolitan Police Agency requested an arrest warrant for Seungri over the following charges: Prostitution Mediation, Embezzlement of Burning Sun funds (according to the police, Seungri directly intervened in the misappropriation of about 200M Won from Burning Sun as brand fee for Monkey Museum), and Monkey Museum's violation of the Food Sanitation Act (For inappropriately declaring Monkey Museum as a restaurant instead of an entertainment establishment).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=213&aid=0001103797|title='\ub274\uc2a48' \uacbd\ucc30, \uc2b9\ub9ac\u00b7\uc720\uc778\uc11d \ub0b4\uc77c(8\uc77c) \uad6c\uc18d\uc601\uc7a5 \uc2e0\uccad|website=entertain.naver.com|language=ko|access-date=August 19, 2019}}</ref> On May 14, Seoul District Court rejected the arrest warrant saying that embezzlement, a major charge, is open to dispute. And it is difficult to acknowledge the reasons for detention, such as the destruction of evidence, for the remaining suspicions which include prostitution mediation.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://n.news.naver.com/article/052/0001294069|title=\uacbd\ucc30 \"\uc2b9\ub9ac \uc601\uc7a5 \uc7ac\uc2e0\uccad \ud604\uc7ac\ub85c\uc36c \uc5b4\ub824\uc6cc\"|website=n.news.naver.com|language=ko|access-date=August 19, 2019}}</ref> On May 15, Police stated that it would be difficult to reapply for  arrest warrant, and they would finalize the investigation prior to Seungri's military enlistment date.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://n.news.naver.com/article/008/0004218664|title=\uc2b9\ub9ac '\uad6c\uc18d \ubd88\ubc1c', \uacbd\ucc30 \"\ubc95\uc6d0 \ud310\ub2e8 \uc874\uc911\u2026\uc7ac\uc2e0\uccad \uc548\ud574\"|website=n.news.naver.com|language=ko|access-date=August 19, 2019}}</ref> However, on June 25, the police stated that his case has been forwarded to prosecution with seven charges: procuring sex service, prostitution mediation, embezzlement of business funds for hiring a legal representative, embezzlement of club Burning Sun revenues, attempt at destruction of evidence, distribution of illegally-filmed content via social platforms, and violation of the Food Sanitation Act.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/now/read?oid=609&aid=0000128782|title=\uc2b9\ub9ac, \uc131\ub9e4\ub9e4\uc54c\uc120-\ud6a1\ub839 \ub4f1 7\uac1c \ud610\uc758\ub85c \uac80\ucc30 \uc1a1\uce58|website=entertain.naver.com|language=ko|access-date=August 19, 2019}}</ref><ref>http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20190820000646</ref>\n\nOn August 28, 2019, Seungri was questioned in connection with illegal gambling.<ref>https://www.scmp.com/news/asia/east-asia/article/3024643/k-pop-scandal-seungri-questioned-police-over-las-vegas-gambling</ref><ref>https://variety.com/2019/music/asia/k-pop-scandal-yg-pair-questioned-by-police-seungri-admits-some-charges-1203317850/</ref> On January 10, 2020, the prosecution announced they had requested a second arrest warrant for Seungri on seven charges.<ref>{{cite web|last=Ock|first=Hyun-ju|title=[Newsmaker] Arrest warrant sought for Seungri over procuring prostitutes, illegal gambling|url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20200110000439|date=January 10, 2020|work=[[The Korea Herald]]|accessdate=January 10, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Other ventures==\n\n===Business ventures===\n[[File:Seungri During Gatsby's Fantastic Festival - 2.jpg|thumb|upright|230px|Seungri DJing at D-Bridge Lounge, [[Cheongdam-dong|Cheongdam]], in 2015.]]\n\nSeungri has helped establish two branches of a music and dance academy called \"Plug In Music Academy,\" also known as \"Seungri Academy\". The dance academy is located in [[Gwangju]], [[Daejeon]], [[Mokpo]], and [[Seoul]]. Students of the academy learn how to sing, dance, and act. Some of the past students of the academy include high-profile K-pop celebrities such as 2NE1's Minzy, BTS' Jung Hoseok, Kara's Goo Hara, TVXQ's Yunho and B.A.P.'s Zelo.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kpopherald.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=201608311751071139664_2|title=Pre-debut photos and anecdotes of Big Bang|date=August 31, 2016|website=Kpop Herald}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/news/culture/2013/04/386_133653.html|title=Celebs build up wealth with '2nd' job|date=April 9, 2013|website=The Korea Times}}</ref><ref name=cafe>{{cite web|url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20160126000475|title=[SUPER RICH] Big Bang net worth 40b won|date=January 26, 2016|website=The Korea Herald}}</ref>\n\nIn 2014, Seungri started a caf\u00e9 business. Purchasing a license for traditional Belgian waffles, he opened a waffle caf\u00e9 ''And Here'' at Daehangno which he left to his mother to run.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://english.visitseoul.net/Hallyu/And-Here_/16355?curPage=5|title=And Here|website=Visit Seoul|access-date=February 23, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180731031724/http://english.visitseoul.net/Hallyu/And-Here_/16355?curPage=5|archive-date=July 31, 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name=cafe /> \nSeungri opened his private bar called ''Monkey Museum'' night club in [[Changsha]], [[Hunan]], China in partnership with Luk Hing Entertainment.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://en.acnnewswire.com/press-release/english/34506/luk-hing-entertainment-joins-hands-with-seungri-in-tapping-the-prc-premium-clubbing-and-entertainment-market|title=Luk Hing Entertainment Joins Hands with Seungri in Tapping the PRC Premium Clubbing and Entertainment Market|work=ACN Newswire|accessdate=January 27, 2017}}</ref> He also founded a record label ''Natural High Record'' alongside other [[DJ]]s.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://yes-news.com/60312/11\u670811\u65e5BIGBANG\u52dd\u5229\u99d5\u5230Club-Cubic\u5973\u58eb\u76db\u88dd\u51fa\u5e2d\u66f4\u53ef\u7372\u514d\u8cbb\u5165\u5834|title=11\u670811\u65e5BIGBANG\u52dd\u5229\u99d5\u5230Club Cubic\uff01\u5973\u58eb\u76db\u88dd\u51fa\u5e2d\u66f4\u53ef\u7372\u514d\u8cbb\u5165\u5834\uff01|work=Yes News|accessdate=January 27, 2017}}</ref> In December 2016, he launched a Japanese ramen restaurant franchise called Aori Ramen in Seoul.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.joins.com/article/21141679|script-title=ko:\"\uc2b9\ub9ac \uc798 \ub098\uac00\ub124\" \ub124\ud2f0\uc98c\ub4e4\uc774 \uc2b9\ub9ac \uadfc\ud669\uc5d0 \ub180\ub780 \uc774\uc720|website=JoongAng Ilbo|date=January 19, 2017|language=ko}}</ref> During 2017, the franchise expanded through Asia,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.joins.com/article/22175342|script-title=ko:\u2018\uc911\uad6d\u00b7\ub3d9\ub0a8\uc544 \uc9c4\ucd9c\u2019 \ube45\ubc45 \uba64\ubc84 \uc2b9\ub9ac\uc758 \ub77c\uba58\uc0ac\uc5c5 \uadfc\ud669|date=December 5, 2017|website=JoongAng Ilbo|language=ko}}</ref> and in November, he announced that he would open the 15th branch in [[Kuala Lumpur]].<ref>{{citeweb|url=https://sg.news.yahoo.com/seungri-apos-ramen-joint-open-062300048.html|title=Seungri's ramen joint to open in Malaysia soon|work=Yahoo! |date=November 14, 2017}}</ref> In early 2017, he invested in the medical cosmetic brand Dr. Gloderm, acquiring 10% of the cosmetic company's shares.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=016&aid=0001332967|script-title=ko:\ube45\ubc45 \uc2b9\ub9ac, \uc815\uc720\ub144 \uc5f0\ub9d0\uc744 \ub728\uac81\uac8c \ub2ec\uad70\ub2e4|date=December 26, 2017|website=Naver|publisher=Herald Corporation|language=ko}}</ref> Seungri now has a company name for all his investments under YURI HOLDINGS.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.yuriholdings.com/|title=Yuri Holdings|website=Official Website}}</ref>\n\nIn 2018, Seungri was revealed to be collaborating with Liquid State, an electronic dance music label newly launched by Sony Music Entertainment and Tencent Music Entertainment. He would serve as the label's ambassador and be involved in music collaborations.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kpopherald.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=201802011811093707876_2|title=Big Bang\u2019s Seungri, Junkilla join forces with new Asia-based music label|date=February 1, 2018|website=Kpop Herald}}</ref> In June, Seungri become the CEO of ''YGX'', a label under YG Entertainment, Seungri will work on recruiting talented hip-hop rookies and running entertainment businesses. The label company was merged with Seungri's DJ label ''Natural High Record'', it will also be in charge of [[YG Entertainment#HIGHGRND|HIGHGRND]] and a dance academy called YGX Academy.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thejakartapost.com/life/2018/06/06/seungri-soars-as-solo-artist.html|title=Seungri soars as solo artist|date=June 6, 2018|website=The Jakarta Post}}</ref> In 2019, he resigned from all management positions before his military enlistment, as required by Korean law.\n\n===Sports===\nIn May 2015, [[FC MEN]] announced through their instagram that Seungri would be joining their celebrity soccer club. He was given the forward position and the number 11.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.soompi.com/2015/05/26/bigbangs-seungri-joins-celebrity-soccer-team-fc-men/|title=BIGBANG's Seungri Joins Celebrity Soccer Team FC MEN|last=an0ya|website=Soompi|access-date=March 27, 2016}}</ref>\n\nSeungri, under the name Richard Lee, participated in his first [[jiu-jitsu]] match under the Japan Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu Federation in 2017. He won two medals, silver medal in adult white open-weight class and bronze medal for adult white featherweight class. He also earned a [[Black belt (martial arts)|black belt]] in [[taekwondo]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sbs.com.au/popasia/blog/2017/07/18/bigbangs-seungri-jiu-jitsu-master|title=BIGBANG's Seungri is a Jiu-Jitsu master|work=SBS PopAsia|accessdate=August 3, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://efight.jp/result-20170803_265082|title=\u3010\u67d4\u8853\u3011\u97d3\u56fd\u4eba\u6c17\u30b0\u30eb\u30fc\u30d7BIGBANG\u306eV.I\u304c\u516c\u5f0f\u6226\u30c7\u30d3\u30e5\u30fc\u3067\u6e96\u512a\u52dd|work=E Fight|accessdate=August 3, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kpopstarz.com/articles/285434/20170622/bigbang-seungri-to-compete-in-jiu-jitsu-tournament-in-new-york.htm|title=BIGBANG Seungri To Compete In Jiu Jitsu Tournament in New York|work=KPopStarz|accessdate=August 3, 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Philanthropy===\nIn 2015, Seungri joined label-mate Sean for a briquette charity. He had previously promised fans to deliver and donate 30,000 briquettes but donated a total of 130,000. He brought along notable celebrities to the charity, including [[F.T. Island]]'s [[Choi Jong-hoon]] and [[Jung Joon-young]] of [[Drug Restaurant]] (formerly JJY).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.koogle.tv/media/news/bigbangs-seungri-sean-join-hands-for-seoul-briquette-charity/|title=BIGBANG's Seungri & Sean Join Hands for Seoul Briquette Charity|date=December 29, 2015|website=Koogle}}</ref>\n\nIn December 2017, Seungri, along with 30 Aori Ramen employees and his father, delivered coal briquettes to low-income families for cooking and heating their homes.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.sbs.co.kr/news/endPage.do?news_id=N1004526904&oaid=N1004624779&plink=REL&cooper=SBSNEWSEND|title=BIGBANG SEUNGRI Helps Low-Income Family to Spend Warm Winter|date=December 12, 2017|website=SBS News}}</ref> He also donated 100 million won to global children welfare agency [[ChildFund|ChildFund Korea]].<ref>{{citeweb|url=https://www.nst.com.my/lifestyle/groove/2017/12/314279/seungri-donates-poor-birthday |title= Seungri donates to poor on birthday|date=December 14, 2017|work=The Straits Times}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nAfter passing his college entrance exams, Seungri was accepted by [[Chung-Ang University]] and began his college education in the spring of 2010, along with [[Kwon Yuri|Yuri]] and [[Sooyoung]] of [[Girls' Generation]].<ref name=\"\uc18c\uc2dc \uc11c\ud604\u00b7\uc720\ub9ac-\ube45\ubc45 \uc2b9\ub9ac \ub3d9\uad6d\ub300 \uc5f0\uc601\uacfc \uc218\uc2dc \ucd5c\uc885\ud569\uaca9\">{{cite news | first= | last= | author2= | title=\uc18c\uc2dc \uc11c\ud604\u00b7\uc720\ub9ac-\ube45\ubc45 \uc2b9\ub9ac \ub3d9\uad6d\ub300 \uc5f0\uc601\uacfc \uc218\uc2dc \ucd5c\uc885\ud569\uaca9|date=November 5, 2009| publisher= | url =http://www.newsen.com/news_view.php?uid=200911051749081001| work= Newsen| pages = | accessdate = January 22, 2010 }}</ref> He dropped out of Chung-Ang University in 2012 after being placed on academic probation several times due to his demanding schedule with Big Bang,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hancinema.net/big-bang-s-seungri-drops-out-of-current-university-39888.html|title=Big Bang's Seungri Drops Out Of Current University|date=March 12, 2012|website=Hancinema|publisher=KBS World}}</ref> opting instead to enroll at Gukje Digital University so he could take online classes and attend his schedules at the same time.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sg.news.yahoo.com/seung-ri-drops-university-study-online-062000221.html|title=Seung-ri drops university to study online|date=March 13, 2012|website=Yahoo}}</ref>\n\nSeungri is a [[Polyglotism|polyglot]]; he speaks several languages including [[Korean language|Korean]], [[English language|English]], [[Japanese language|Japanese]],\n[[Mandarin Chinese|Mandarin]] and is currently learning [[Cantonese language|Cantonese]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.nate.com/view/20180208n39566?mid=n1008|title=\"\ub354\ube59NO\u00b7\ud1b5\uc5edNO\"\u2026'\u4e2d \uc9c4\ucd9c' \uc2b9\ub9ac, \uc720\ucc3d\ud55c \uc911\uad6d\uc5b4 '\ub300\ub959\ub3c4 \ud640\ub9ad'|date=February 8, 2018|website=Nate|language=ko}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.yg-life.com/archives/73674?lang=en|title=BIGBANG\u2019s SEUNGRI starring in Japanese movie\u2026 \"Really happy to get such suggestion\"|date=April 22, 2016|website=YG Life}}</ref>\n\n===Mandatory military service===\nSeungri was set to enlist in Nonsan Army Training Center on March 25, 2019,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/now/read?oid=018&aid=0004326395|script-title=ko:[\ub2e8\ub3c5] \uc2b9\ub9ac, 25\uc77c \uc721\uad70 \ud604\uc5ed \uc785\ub300 \"\uc758\uacbd \ud3ec\uae30\"|website=[[Naver]]|language=ko|date=March 8, 2019|access-date=March 11, 2019}}</ref> despite ongoing controversies regarding the [[Burning Sun scandal]]. Following the investigation, Seungri put in a request for the [[Conscription in South Korea|conscription]] delay,<ref>{{cite news|title=Seungri to postpone military duty; Jung hands out 'golden phone'|url=http://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/nation/2019/03/251_265416.html|publisher=[[The Korea Times]]|date=March 15, 2019|accessdate=March 15, 2019}}</ref> and the [[Military Manpower Administration]] granted a three-month postponement.<ref>{{cite news|title=[Newsmaker] Seungri postpones military amid Burning Sun investigation|url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20190320000704|publisher=[[The Korea Herald]]|date=March 20, 2019|first=Ju-young|last=Park|accessdate=March 20, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=[Newsmaker] Military recruitment agency okays Seungri's request for draft delay|url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20190320000439|publisher=[[The Korea Herald]]|date=March 20, 2019|accessdate=March 20, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn March 9, 2020, Seungri enlisted in the military at the 6th Infantry Recruit Training Center in [[Cheorwon County]], [[Gangwon Province, South Korea|Gangwon Province]]. He did not answer any of the press' questions on his way to the training center.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.xportsnews.com/?ac=article_view&entry_id=1244811|title=\u2018\ud574\uc678 \uc6d0\uc815 \ub3c4\ubc15 \ubc0f \uc131\ub9e4\ub9e4 \uc54c\uc120 \ud610\uc758\u2019 \uc2b9\ub9ac, \uc624\ub298 \uc785\ub300[\uc5d1's HD\ud3ec\ud1a0]|date=March 9, 2020|website=www.xportsnews.com|language=ko|access-date=March 11, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Discography ==\n{{Main|Seungri discography}}\n{{See also|Big Bang discography}}\n* ''[[The Great Seungri]]'' (2018)\n\n== Filmography ==\n{{See also|Big Bang filmography}}\n\n=== Film ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Year\n! Film\n! Role\n|-\n| 2009\n| ''[[19-Nineteen|Nineteen]]''\n| Park Min-seo\n|-\n| 2009\n| ''Why Did You Come to My House?''\n| Park Ji-min\n|-\n| 2016\t\n| ''[[Big Bang Made]]''\t\n| Himself\n|-\n| 2016\n| ''[[High & Low: The Movie]]''\n| Lee\n|-\n| 2018\n|''Love Only''\n|Winson / Yun Sheng \n|}\n\n===Television series===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Network\n|-\n| 2010\n| ''Haru''\n| Cameo\n|\n|-\n| 2011\n| ''[[Lights and Shadows (TV series)|Lights and Shadows]]''\n| Ahn Jae-su (cameo, ep 9-10)\n| ''[[Munhwa Broadcasting Corporation|MBC]]''\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''Kindaichi Shonen no Jikenbo (The Files of Young Kindaichi - Lost in Kowloon)''\n| Kim Yong-dong\n| [[Nippon TV|NTV]]\n|-\n| 2013-2014\n| ''Yubikoi ~Kimini Okuru Message~ - A Message Send To You''\n| Han Seung-ho\n| \n|-\n| 2014\n| ''[[Angel Eyes (TV series)|Angel Eyes]]''\n| Teddy Seo\n| ''[[Seoul Broadcasting System|SBS]]''\n|-\n|}\n\n=== Musical ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n|-\n| 2008\n| ''Sonagi''\n|\n|-\n| 2009 \n| ''Shouting! (\uc18c\ub9ac\uccd0!)''\n|\n|-\n|}\n\n===Variety show===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Year\n!Channel\n!Title\n!Role\n!Other\n|-\n|2008-2009\n|rowspan=2|[[Munhwa Broadcasting Corporation|MBC]]\n|''[[Music Core|Show! Music Core]]''\n|Co-host\n|with [[Daesung]]\n|-\n|2010\n|''[[Sunday Night (South Korean TV series)#Enjoy Today|Enjoy Today]]''\n|Host\n|\n|- \n|2012\n|[[Space Shower TV]]\n|''Seung-chan's Complete Victory Declaration'' \n|Cast member\n| Reality show \n|-\n|rows