te\"\n| {{nom}}\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://spellemann.no/nominerte-spellemannprisen-2018/ |website=Spellemann |title=Nominerte Spellemannprisen 2018 |accessdate=February 10, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n==Tours==\n{{Main|List of Big Bang solo concert tours}}\n{{See also|List of Big Bang concert tours}}\n* [[The Great Seungri (tour)|The Great Seungri]] (2018)\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n<!--per [[WP:EL]], ONE official site may be listed. This is not an SNS directory.-->\n{{commons category|Seungri}}\n*{{Twitter|ForvictoRi}}\n*{{IMDb name|3411281}}\n*{{Kmdb person|00050607}}\n*{{HanCinema person}}\n\n{{Seungri}}\n{{Big Bang}}\n{{YG Entertainment}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Seungri| ]]\n[[Category:1990 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Big Bang (South Korean band) members]]\n[[Category:Chung-Ang University alumni]]\n[[Category:King of Mask Singer contestants]]\n[[Category:Nightclub owners]]\n[[Category:People from Gwangju]]\n[[Category:South Korean child singers]]\n[[Category:South Korean investors]]\n[[Category:South Korean male film actors]]\n[[Category:South Korean male idols]]\n[[Category:South Korean male musical theatre actors]]\n[[Category:South Korean male singers]]\n[[Category:South Korean male television actors]]\n[[Category:South Korean music industry executives]]\n[[Category:South Korean pop singers]]\n[[Category:South Korean restaurateurs]]\n[[Category:South Korean rhythm and blues singers]]\n[[Category:South Korean television personalities]]\n[[Category:YG Entertainment artists]]\n", "name_user": "Lijalina", "label": "safe", "comment": "Early beginnings and debut with Big Bang", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Seungri"}
{"title_page": "Neuwesteel", "text_new": "{{Infobox Ortsteil einer Gemeinde in Deutschland\n| name               = Neuwesteel\n| Art            = Stadtteil\n| Town           = [[Norden, Lower Saxony|Norden]]\n| Wappen             = Wappen von Neuwesteel.png\n|coordinates       = {{coord|53|32|13|N|07|9|37|E|format=dms|display=inline,title}}\n| Bundesland             = Lower Saxony\n| H\u00f6he                   = 1 <!-- Quelle: Geodatenzentrum -->\n| Fl\u00e4che                 = 15.068\n| Einwohner              = 337\n| Stand= 2016-12-31\n| Postleitzahl          = 26506\n| Vorwahl               = 04931\n| Lageplan              = Norden-Neuwesteel.svg\n| Lageplanbeschreibung = Lage von Neuwesteel im Stadtgebiet von Norden\n}}\n\n'''Neuwesteel''' is part of the borough of [[Norden (Ostfriesland)|Norden]] in [[East Frisia]] in the northwest of the German state of [[Lower Saxony]]. It is the third most recent quarter after [[Tidofeld]] and [[Leybuchtpolder]], because it was only founded on 11 July 1934.<ref>[http://www.norden.de/index.phtml?La=1&sNavID=549.48&mNavID=1.100&object=tx|1652.526.1&sub=0 Stadtteilseite auf www.norden.de]</ref>\n\nOn the terrain of the present parish lay the village of Westeel which was submerged in 1373 when the [[Leybucht]] bay flooded the area. Parts of the Leybucht were then dyked over the course of the centuries. In earlier centuries this was done manually and using spades, which is why the spade forms part of the Neuwesteel coat of arms. In the years 1928 and 1929 the roughly 600-[[hectare]] Leypolder was dyked.<ref>Eberhard Rack: Kleine Landeskunde Ostfrieslands, Isensee Verlag, Oldenburg 1998, p. 92</ref> On this [[polder]] has stood the village of Neuwesteel since 1934. Initially it was part of the municipality of ''S\u00fcderpolder''. On 1 October the whole municipality of S\u00fcderpolder was renamed ''Neuwesteel''.<ref>[http://www.geschichte-on-demand.de/norden.html verwaltungsgeschichte.de: Landkreis Norden]</ref>\n\nThe municipality of Neuwesteel became part of the collective municipality of Leybucht in 1965. As part of the territorial reforms in Lower Saxony in 1972 Neuwesteel was incorporated into the borough of Norden. As an incorporated subdistrict Neuwesteel still has a parish chairman (''Ortsvorsteher''), who represents the concerns of the roughly 340 inhabitants<ref>[http://www.norden.de/index.phtml?mNavID=549.20&sNavID=549.20&La=1#5 Norden.de: Einwohnerzahl nach Ortsteilen]</ref> to the borough of Norden.\n\nBecause the dyked polder soil is very fertile, the region was used from the very beginning for agricultural purposes. Cattle farming and crops predominate, especially the cultivation of potatoes.\n\nIn Neuwesteel is the Leybucht Pumping Station, part of the Drainage Association of Norden, which ensures that the lower lying areas are drained via the [[Norder Tief]]. In addition to the pumping station is a campsite. Because there are no bridges for several kilometres along the Norder Tief, the river may be crossed in Neuwesteel on a ''[[P\u00fcnte]]'', a type of raft. However, it is only for pedestrians and cyclists.\n\n== References ==\n<references />\n\n{{Norden (East Frisia)}}\n\n[[Category:Aurich (district)]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Ortsteil einer Gemeinde in Deutschland\n| Ortsteil               = Neuwesteel\n| Art            = Stadtteil\n| Town           = [[Norden, Lower Saxony|Norden]]\n| Wappen             = Wappen von Neuwesteel.png\n|coordinates       = {{coord|53|32|13|N|07|9|37|E|format=dms|display=inline,title}}\n| Bundesland             = Lower Saxony\n| H\u00f6he                   = 1 <!-- Quelle: Geodatenzentrum -->\n| Fl\u00e4che                 = 15.068\n| Einwohner              = 337\n| Stand= 2016-12-31\n| Eingemeindungsdatum    =\n| Postleitzahl          = 26506\n| Vorwahl               = 04931\n| Lageplan              = Norden-Neuwesteel.svg\n| Lageplanbeschreibung = Lage von Neuwesteel im Stadtgebiet von Norden\n}}\n\n'''Neuwesteel''' is part of the borough of [[Norden (Ostfriesland)|Norden]] in [[East Frisia]] in the northwest of the German state of [[Lower Saxony]]. It is the third most recent quarter after [[Tidofeld]] and [[Leybuchtpolder]], because it was only founded on 11 July 1934.<ref>[http://www.norden.de/index.phtml?La=1&sNavID=549.48&mNavID=1.100&object=tx|1652.526.1&sub=0 Stadtteilseite auf www.norden.de]</ref>\n\nOn the terrain of the present parish lay the village of Westeel which was submerged in 1373 when the [[Leybucht]] bay flooded the area. Parts of the Leybucht were then dyked over the course of the centuries. In earlier centuries this was done manually and using spades, which is why the spade forms part of the Neuwesteel coat of arms. In the years 1928 and 1929 the roughly 600-[[hectare]] Leypolder was dyked.<ref>Eberhard Rack: Kleine Landeskunde Ostfrieslands, Isensee Verlag, Oldenburg 1998, p. 92</ref> On this [[polder]] has stood the village of Neuwesteel since 1934. Initially it was part of the municipality of ''S\u00fcderpolder''. On 1 October the whole municipality of S\u00fcderpolder was renamed ''Neuwesteel''.<ref>[http://www.geschichte-on-demand.de/norden.html verwaltungsgeschichte.de: Landkreis Norden]</ref>\n\nThe municipality of Neuwesteel became part of the collective municipality of Leybucht in 1965. As part of the territorial reforms in Lower Saxony in 1972 Neuwesteel was incorporated into the borough of Norden. As an incorporated subdistrict Neuwesteel still has a parish chairman (''Ortsvorsteher''), who represents the concerns of the roughly 340 inhabitants<ref>[http://www.norden.de/index.phtml?mNavID=549.20&sNavID=549.20&La=1#5 Norden.de: Einwohnerzahl nach Ortsteilen]</ref> to the borough of Norden.\n\nBecause the dyked polder soil is very fertile, the region was used from the very beginning for agricultural purposes. Cattle farming and crops predominate, especially the cultivation of potatoes.\n\nIn Neuwesteel is the Leybucht Pumping Station, part of the Drainage Association of Norden, which ensures that the lower lying areas are drained via the [[Norder Tief]]. In addition to the pumping station is a campsite. Because there are no bridges for several kilometres along the Norder Tief, the river may be crossed in Neuwesteel on a ''[[P\u00fcnte]]'', a type of raft. However, it is only for pedestrians and cyclists.\n\n== References ==\n<references />\n\n{{Norden (East Frisia)}}\n\n[[Category:Aurich (district)]]\n", "name_user": "Markussep", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Neuwesteel"}
